<TITLE> BDR man held in Rangpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangpur, Mar 8 (bdnews24.com)  A BDR member who had been on the run after the mutiny at the Pilkhana headquarters was arrested Sunday, police said. BDR authorities detained Shahab Uddin after he had gone to join duty at Rangpur BDR sector headquarters, Abdur Rashid, Kotwali police chief told bdnews24.com. He was handed in to the police, who sent him to jail, Rashid said. He could not give any reasonable explanation for his absence from duty despite the government deadline, Rashid said. Shahab Uddin, son of Rezaul Karim, is from Godagari Upazila in Rajshahi, Rashid said. The police officer further said Godagari police were gathering information about the arrestee's activities after they notified them. 
